 this book critique both historical and current practices and suggest several pragmatic options, highlighting the role of education in attaining these noble yet unachieved objectives. This book represents a welcome addition to the human rights and global citizenship literature and provides ideas for new platforms that are human rights friendly and expansively attuned toward global citizenship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aEducation : Foundations of Education. 4aEducation : Social Context of Education. 4aPolitics and Law : Human Rights. 4aPolitics and Law : Peace. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aAbdi, Ali A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbdi, Ali A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDower, Nigel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Derek G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGhosh, Ratna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuo, Shibao, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuaman, Hilaria Supa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJames, Carl E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKachur, Jerrold L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKapoor, Dip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoenig, Shulamith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPike, Graham, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichardson, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSamek, Toni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShultz, Lynette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular